# Agent behavior profiles

When the user cares about **how** the agent collaborates (verbosity, check-ins, exploration style), use the **`agent-behavior`** module via `workspace-kit run` — see **`.ai/AGENT-CLI-MAP.md`** (Tier C).

1. Optional session opener: `workspace-kit run resolve-behavior-profile '{}'` and treat `data.effective` as advisory tone guidance.
2. User unsure: drive `interview-behavior-profile` (`action`: `start` → `answer` → … → `finalize`) or compare builtins with `explain-behavior-profiles`.
3. **Hard layer still wins:** `.ai/PRINCIPLES.md`, policy `policyApproval`, and task acceptance criteria override any profile.

Deep design plan (maintainer narrative, optional): `docs/maintainers/plans/agent-behavior-module.md` — prefer **`src/modules/agent-behavior/README.md`** + **`.ai/AGENT-CLI-MAP.md`** for agents.
